The Bank of France said it invited offersof first category paper today for a money market interventiontender.    Money market dealers said conditions seemed right for theBank to cut its intervention rate at the tender by a quarterpercentage point to 7-3/4 pct from eight, reflecting an easingin call money rate last week, and the French franc's steadinesson foreign exchange markets since the February 22 currencystabilisation accord here by the Group of Five and Canada.    Intervention rate was last raised to eight pct from 7-1/4on January 2. Call money today was quoted at 7-11/16 7-3/4 pct. REUTER&#3;